9c6e6c77-20e5-5ece-a6a6-88b15a30bdd8,tg:rubgr:1545,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"

The tapestry design by P. Coeck of the Conversion of Saul ([Georges] Marlier, [La renaissance flamande : Pierre Coeck d'Alost, Bruxelles: Finck, 1966], Fig. 253 & 254) not only important for 'Unfaithful Shepherd' but also for Bruegel's Conversion of Saul: 1) Horse on right seen from back with the rider holding right hand on back; 2) Man (on horseback) shielding himself with raised arm against heavenly light; 3) The great cloud though without Christ in Bruegel.

column4: <content>The tapestry design by P. Coeck of the Conversion of Saul ([Georges] Marlier, [La renaissance flamande : Pierre Coeck d'Alost, Bruxelles: Finck, 1966], Fig. 253 & 254) not only important for 'Unfaithful Shepherd' but also for Bruegel's Conversion of Saul: 1) Horse on right seen from back with the rider holding right hand on back; 2) Man (on horseback) shielding himself with raised arm against heavenly light; 3) The great cloud though without Christ in Bruegel.</content>
